statement.p:
Find \displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx}
in terms of x and y 
if x \ln y + y^{3} = 3 \ln x.

static.solution:
\displaystyle \int u^n du = \frac{u^{n+1}}{n+1}:
\parbox{0.4\textwidth}{

\ \begin{aligned}
\int_{2}^{4} \frac 1 {x^2} dx  \amp  = \int_{2}^{4} x^{-2} dx \\\\ 
\amp  =	\left (-1)x^{-1} \right|_{2}^{4} = \left \frac{-1}{x} \right|_{2}^{4}	\\\\
\amp  =	\frac{-1}{4} - \frac{-1}{2}	= \frac 1 {2} - \frac 1 {4} = 0.25
\end{aligned} }

p.me:
\begin{aligned}
\int_{2}^{9} (4 x + 10) dx \amp=  4 \int_{2}^{9} x\, dx + 10 \int_{2}^{9} dx\\
 \amp=  4 \left( \left. \frac{x^2}{2} \right|_{2}^{9} \right)
                      + 10 \left( \left. x \right|_{2}^{9} \right)\\
 \amp=  4 \left( \frac{9^2}{2} - \frac{2^2}{2} \right)
                      + 10 \left( 9 - 2 \right) = {224}
\end{aligned}

